defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.attribute.show-location.description: Display the current anchor point with direction
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.attribute.show-mute-btn.description: Whether to show the mute button
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.attribute.show-play-btn.description: Whether to display the play button in the control bar at the bottom of the video
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.attribute.show-progress.description: If not set, it will only be displayed when the width is greater than 240
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.attribute.skip-hidden-item-layout.desc: Whether to skip the undisplayed slider layout, set to true to optimize the sliding performance in complex situations, but the layout information of the hidden state slider will be lost
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.attribute.start.description: mode is time: indicates the beginning of the valid time range, the string format is "hh:mm"; mode is date: indicates the beginning of the valid date range, the string format is "YYYY-MM-DD"
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.attribute.step.description: Radio step length, the value must be greater than 0 and divisible by (max-min)
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.attribute.stroke-width.description: The width of the progress bar, in px
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.attribute.target.description: On which target the jump occurs, the current application is the default
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.attribute.title.description: Title of the video, shown at the top when full screen
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.attribute.touchable.description: Whether to listen to user touch events
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.attribute.unit-id.description: Ad unit id, which can be created in the main traffic module of the applet management background
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.attribute.upper-threshold.description: How far away from the top/left (in px), the scrolltoupper event is triggered
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.attribute.url.description: Push stream address. Currently only supports flv, rtmp format
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.attribute.version.description: Valid when target="miniProgram", the version of the mini program to be opened, the valid values are develop (development version), trial (experience version), release (official version), this parameter only when the current mini program is the development version or the experience version Effective; if the current applet is the trial version or the official version, the open applet must be the official version
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.attribute.vertical.description: Whether the sliding direction is vertical
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.attribute.vslide-gesture-in-fullscreen: In full screen mode, whether to turn on the brightness and volume adjustment gestures
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.attribute.vslide-gesture.description: In non-full screen mode, whether to turn on the brightness and volume adjustment gestures (same as page-gesture)
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.attribute.waiting-image-md5.descriptio: MD5 value of waiting screen resource
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.attribute.waiting-image.description: Waiting screen for streaming when entering the background
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.attribute.x.description: Define the offset of the x-axis direction. If the value of x is not within the movable range, it will automatically move to the movable range; changing the value of x will trigger the animation.
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.attribute.y.description: Define the offset of the y-axis direction. If the value of y is not within the movable range, it will automatically move to the movable range; changing the y value will trigger the animation.
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.element.se-checkbox-group.description: Multiple selector, composed of multiple checkboxes
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.element.se-movable-view.description: Movable view container, drag and slide on the page
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.element.se-radio-group.description: Single item selector, composed of multiple radios inside
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.element.se-select.description: The scroll selector that pops up from the bottom now supports five types of selectors, which are distinguished by mode. They are ordinary selector, multi-column selector, time selector, date selector, province city selector, and the default is normal selector Device.
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.element.se-swiper-item.description: Can only be placed in the swiper component, the width and height are automatically set to 100%
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.animationfinish.description: The animationfinish event is triggered when the animation ends，event.detail = {current: current, source: source}
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.blur.description: Triggered when the editor loses focus，detail = {html, text, delta}
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.callouttap.description: Triggered when the bubble corresponding to the marked point is clicked
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.change.description: Event triggered during dragging, event.detail = {x: x, y: y, source: source}. The source represents the reason for the movement, and the value can be touch (drag), touch-out-of-bounds (out of the range of movement), out-of-bounds (rebound after exceeding the range of movement), friction (inertia) and Empty string (setData).
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.click.description: Triggered when the component is clicked
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.columnchange.description: The columnchange event is triggered when the value of a column changes, event.detail = {column: column, value: value}, the value of column indicates which column is changed (subscript starts from 0), and the value of value indicates the subscript of the changed value
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.confirm.description: When you click Finish, the confirm event is triggered，event.detail = {value: value}
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.controltap.description: Triggered when the control is clicked
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.ended.description: The ended event is triggered when the video reaches the end
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.error.description: Trigger error event when an error occurs，detail = {errMsg: 'something wrong'}
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.focus.description: Triggered when the editor is focused，event.detail = {html, text, delta}
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.getuserinfo.description: When the user clicks the button, the obtained user information will be returned, and the callback detail data is the same as that returned by wx.getUserInfo
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.input.description: Triggered when the editor content changes，detail = {html, text, delta}
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.launchapp.description: Callback for successful opening of the app
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.linechange.description: Called when the number of lines in the input box changes，event.detail = {height: 0, heightRpx: 0, lineCount: 0}
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.load.description: When the image is loaded, the event name posted to AppService, event object event.detail = {height:'image height px', width:'image width px'}
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.loadedmetadata.description: Fires when the video metadata is loaded.event.detail = {width, height, duration}
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.longpress.description: After the finger touches, leave after more than 350ms (recommended to use longpress event instead)
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.longtap.description: After the finger touches, it takes more than 350ms to leave. If the event callback function is specified and this event is triggered, the tap event will not be triggered
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.markertap.description: Triggered when the marker is clicked
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.message.description: When the webpage postsMessage to the application, it will trigger and receive the message at a specific time (application back, component destruction, sharing).e.detail = { data }
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.opensetting.description: Call back after opening the authorization setting page
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.pause.description: When the playback is paused, the pause event is triggered
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.play.description: Trigger play event when start/continue playing
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.progress.description: Triggered when the loading progress changes, only one segment of loading is supported. event.detail = {buffered}, percentage
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.ready.description: Triggered when the editor is initialized
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.regionchange.description: Triggered when the field of view changes
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.reset.description: The reset event will be triggered when the form is reset
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.scale.description: Events triggered during zooming，event.detail = {x: x, y: y, scale: scale}。
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.scroll.description: Triggered when scrolling，event.detail = {scrollLeft, scrollTop, scrollHeight, scrollWidth, deltaX, deltaY}
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.scrolltolower.description: Scroll to the bottom/right, the scrolltolower event will be triggered
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.scrolltoupper.description: Scroll to the top/left, the scrolltoupper event will be triggered
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.statuschange.description: Triggered when the style in the editor is changed through the Context method, and returns the style set in the selection
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.stop.description: The camera is triggered when it terminates abnormally, such as exiting the background, etc.
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.submit.description: Carrying the data in the form triggers the submit event, event.detail = {value: {'name':'value'}, formId:''}
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.tap.description: Leave immediately after the finger touches
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.timeupdate.description: Triggered when the playback progress changes, event.detail = {currentTime, duration}. Trigger frequency 250ms once
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.touchcancel.description: Interrupted finger touch action, such as call reminder, pop-up window
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.transition.description: The transition event will be triggered when the position of swiper-item changes，event.detail = {dx: dx, dy: dy}
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.updated.description: Triggered when the map rendering update is complete
defs/html/qh_vue_tag._.event.waiting.description: Triggered when the video is buffered

defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.auto-play.description: Optional value is true/false，The default is false。This value determines whether or not auto rotations are played.Reset the UI associated with LoadMore if the value is different.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.autofocus.description: Boolean data that indicates whether the control automatically gets input focus when the page loads.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.background.description: The bar code identifies the background color of the control, and the color value is supported (refer to CSS color specification) :Color Names (see CSS Color Names) Hexadecimal values RGB values. Default values are black.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.case.description:
Declare the type of the current template. It will be rendered only if the type in the data matches the current type. The semantics are the same as in the programming language case.

There will be at most one match in all templates, and the match will go from top to bottom in the order of the template. Once the match is successful, there will be no further match.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.column-count.description: The number of columns describing the waterfall flow
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.column-gap.description: Column to column gap. If Normal is specified, it corresponds to 32.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.column-width.description: Describes the column width of each column of a waterfall stream
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.default.description: Indicates that the current template is the default template type and does not require a value. If the data item does not match to any case type, the rendering takes the default template. If more than one Default exists, only the first default template will be used.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.disabled.description: Boolean data indicating whether input is supported. Typically the click event is disabled on the Disabled control.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.filters.description: Bar code type filter, bar code type constant array, support QR, EAN 13, EAN 8 types by default.This parameter allows you to set the type of bar code that is supported by scanning recognition(Note: the more barcode types you set to support, the speed of scanning recognition may decrease).
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.for.description:
Adding the for attribute to the recycle-list describes how to loop through the data in the list,
The syntax is similar to Vue's v-for directive, but it loops through its own internal child nodes, not the current node.

The for property can be written in one of two ways:

alias in expression
(alias, index) in expression
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.frameColor.description: Scan box color, color value support (refer to CSS color specification) :Color Names (see CSS Color Names) Hexadecimal value RGB value RGBA value, default value is red.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.href.description: The URL of the page to be jumped. The page to be jumped needs to be a Weex page. If the page to jump to is a plain HTML, this is an undefined behavior.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.index.description: Sets the number of pages on which the slider will be displayed
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.infinite.description: Loops. Optional value is trueFalse. Default value is true.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.interval.description: Value is the number of milliseconds,This value sets the slider toggle interval.Valid when the auto-play value is true.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.keep-index.description: Sets whether the index of the page before the change is maintained after the data in the slider changes
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.keep-scroll-position.descrip: List remains where it was last scrolled after inserting data
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.key.description: Optional property to specify a key value in the list data that can be used as a unique identifier to optimize rendering performance.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.left-gap.description: The gap between the cell on the left and the list. If not specified, it corresponds to 0
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.lines.description: Controls the maximum number of lines of input
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.loadmoreoffset.description: The default value is 0, which is the vertical offset (the distance between the bottom of the device screen and the bottom of the list) needed to trigger the LoadMore event.The loadMore event is emitted when the list's scrollbar gets close enough to the bottom of the list.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.max-length.description: Controls the maximum length of the input
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.max.description: Controls the maximum time to select a date when the type attribute is DATE. The format is yyyy-MM-dd
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.maxlength.description: A value of numeric type that represents the maximum length of the input.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.min.description: Controls the minimum time to select a date when the type attribute is DATE. The format is yyyy-MM-dd
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.offset-accuracy.description: Controls the frequency of onscroll events. The default value is 10, which means that the list has scrolled at least 10 px between onscroll events.Note that setting this value to a smaller value will improve the accuracy of the scrolling event sampling, but will also degrade the performance of the page.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.offset-x-accuracy.descriptio: Controls how often onscroll events occur. The default value is 10, which means that the Slider Page has scrolled at least 10px between onscroll events.Note that setting this value to a smaller value will improve the accuracy of the scrolling event sampling, but will also degrade the performance of the page.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.placeholder.description:
When used as an attribute of image:
The URL of the placeholder map, which will be deleted when the image represented by SRC has been downloaded and displayed. The sample
When used as an attribute of input:
Prompts the user what he can type. The prompt text cannot have carriage returns or line feeds.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.play-status.description: Optional value is play | pause，Used to control the playing state of the video，play or pause，The default value is pause。
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.return-key-type.description: Keyboard return key type, supported defalut;go;next;search;send,done。
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.right-gap.description: The gap between the cell and the list on the right. If not specified, it corresponds to 0
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.rows.description: Receive data of type Number, specifying the height of the component. Default is 2
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.scanbarColor.description: Scan code bar color, color value support (refer to CSS color specification) :Color Names (see CSS Color Names) Hexadecimal value RGB value RGBA value, default value is red.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.scroll-direction.description: You can choose horizontal or vertical, the default value is vertical. Define the direction of scrolling.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.scrollable.description: Sets whether slider pages can be switched by swiping gestures
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.show-scrollbar.description: Optional value is true/ false，The default value is true. Controls whether scroll bars appear.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.singleline.description: Controls whether content is allowed only on a single line
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.src.description: To display the URL of the image, the property is <image> A mandatory property for the component。
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.switch.description:
The switch attribute in the RECYCLE-LIST can be used to specify the name of the field used for the extent-molecule template type in the data.The semantics are the same as the switch in the programming language and are used in conjunction with the case and default attributes of cell-slot.

If the switch attribute is omitted, only the first cell-slot will be treated as a template, and additional templates will be ignored.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.type.description: The input type，Dynamic modification is not supported，Default type is text
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.attribute.value.description: The default content of the component.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.element.a.description:
Used to realize the jump between pages.
Reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/a.html
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.element.a.remarks: Can't be <a> Add anonymous text directly to the,Please use <text> Wrap text.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.element.barcode.description:
App side nvue special scanning code components
reference
https://uniapp.dcloud.io/component/barcode
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.element.barcode.example: <barcode id='1' class="barcode" autostart="true" ref="barcode" background="rgb(0,0,0)" frameColor="#1C86EE" scanbarColor="#1C86EE" :filters="fil" @marked="success" @error="fail"></barcode>
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.element.cell-slot.description: The cell-slot represents the template for each item in the list and is used only to describe the structure of the template, not the actual node.The number of cell-slots represents only the type of template; the number of real list items is determined by the data.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.element.cell.description:
Used to define sublist items in a list, similar to ul for li in HTML. WEEX will efficiently recycle the cell memory to achieve better performance,The component must be a sub-component of the List Recycler Waterfall component,This is to optimize performance while scrolling.
Reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/cell.html
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.element.div.description:
div component is the most basic container for wrapping other components. Supports all common styles, features, and flexbox layouts. It is similar to an HTML div container, but you can't add text (strings) directly to it. If you want to display text, you should use the Text component.In the historical version, the alias for div was container, which is now deprecated.
Reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/div.html
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.element.div.remarks: <div> The nesting level should not be too deep, otherwise it may cause performance problems. It is recommended to control it within 10 layers.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.element.image.description:
Image is used to display a single image in an interface.
Reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/image.html
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.element.image.remarks: Note: You must specify the width and height in the style, otherwise it will not work.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.element.indicator.description: The Indicator component is usually used to display the rotating-map indicator effect and must be used as a child of the Slider component.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.element.input.description:
Weex's built-in Input component is used to create an input component that accepts user input characters. The input component works differently depending on the value of the type attribute, such as text, password, URL, email, tel, etc.
Reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/input.html
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.element.input.remarks: Click events are not supported for this component. Listen for input or change instead of click events.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.element.list.description:
The List component is the core component that provides vertical list functionality, with smooth scrolling and efficient memory management, and is ideal for long list presentation.The simplest way to use it is to populate a list tag with a set of cell tags generated by a simple array repeat.
Reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/list.html
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.element.loading.description:
Loading provides a pull-up loading capability for the container, and its use and properties are similar to refresh.
Reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/loading.html
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.element.recycle-list.description:
The RECYCL-LIST is a new list container with the ability to recycle and reuse, greatly optimizing memory footprint and rendering performance. Only cell-slot can be used as its immediate child node; no other node can be used.
Reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/recycle-list.html
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.element.recycle-list.example:
It is used in the upper-level syntax as follows:

<recycle-list for="(item, i) in longList" switch="type">
  <cell-slot case="A">
    <text>- A {{i}} -</text>
  </cell-slot>
  <cell-slot case="B">
    <text>- B {{i}} -</text>
  </cell-slot>
</recycle-list>
If you have the following data:

const longList = [
  { type: 'A' },
  { type: 'B' },
  { type: 'B' },
  { type: 'A' },
  { type: 'B' }
]
The following equivalent nodes are generated:

<text>- A 0 -</text>
<text>- B 1 -</text>
<text>- B 2 -</text>
<text>- A 3 -</text>
<text>- B 4 -</text>
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.element.refresh.description:
Refresh provides a drop-down refresh function for the container, and its usage and properties are similar to Loading.
Reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/refresh.html
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.element.scroller.description:
The Scroller is a vertical roller that can accommodate multiple sub-components in a row.All child components are scrollable if their total height is higher than themselves.
Reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/scroller.html
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.element.slider.description:
The slider component is used to display multiple images on a page, and on the front end, this effect is known as rotated graphics.
Reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/slider.html
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.element.text.description:
Text is a built-in Weex component that renders text in a specified style.Text can only contain text values. You can insert variable values as text content using the {{}} tag.
Reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/text.html
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.element.text.remarks: If you want to preserve the header and trailing space, you can only write the header and trailing space through the data binding for the time being.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.element.textarea.description:
Textarea is a built-in component of Weex for user interaction and acceptance of user input data. Think of it as input that allows multiple lines
Reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/textarea.html
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.element.textarea.remarks: TextArea supports all events supported by Input.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.element.video.description:
The Video component allows us to embed video content in Weex pages.
Reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/video.html
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.element.waterfall.description:
Components that provide a waterfall flow layout
Reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/waterfall.html
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.element.web.description:
Web is used to display the content of the page specified by the SRC attribute in the weex page.You can also use the WebView module to control the behavior of the WebView, such as fallback, forward, and reload. See the WebView Module for more information.
Reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/web.html
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.event.appear.description: If a component in a scrollable area is bound to the Appear event, the event is triggered when the component's state becomes visible on the screen.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.event.change.description: Triggered when user input is complete. Usually after the blur event.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.event.click.description: Triggered when a click gesture occurs on a component.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.event.disappear.description: If a component that is in a scrollable region has a bound disappear event, the event is emitted when the component is slid off the screen and becomes invisible.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.event.error.description: Barcode identifies error events，event = {type, message, code}
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.event.fail.description: Triggered when playback status is Failed
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.event.finish.description: Triggered when the playback's state is Finished
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.event.input.description: The value of the input character changes.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.event.load.description: The LOAD event is triggered when the image specified by SRC has been loaded.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.event.loadmore.description: If the list scrolls down to the bottom, this event will trigger immediately, and you can load the next page of the list item in the handler of this event.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.event.longpress.description: If a component is bound to the LongPress event, then the event will be emitted when the user holds the component.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.event.marked.description: The bar code identifies successful events，event = {type, message, code, file}
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.event.pagefinish.description: PageFinish event, which is called when the Web page finishes loading.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.event.pagestart.description: The pagestart event is called when the Web page begins to load.
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.event.pause.description: Triggered when the playback's state is Paused
defs/html/uni_nvue_html._.event.pullingdown.description:
Triggered when pulled down, dy, pullingDistance, viewEight, and type can be retrieved from the Event parameter object 
dy: The difference between the sliding distance between the two callbacks
pullingDistance: Dropdown distance
viewHeight: refresh Component height
type: “pullingdown” Constant string

defs/html/uni_vue_tag._.event.scrolltolower.description: Scroll to the bottom right, it will trigger the scrolltolower event
defs/html/uni_vue_tag._.event.scrolltoupper.description: Scroll to the top left, it will trigger the scrolltoupper event
defs/html/uni_vue_tag._.event.statuschange.description: Triggered when changing a style in the editor through the Context method. Returns the selection of the set style
defs/html/uni_vue_tag._.event.stop.description: The camera is triggered when it terminates abnormally, such as exiting the background, etc.
defs/html/uni_vue_tag._.event.submit.description: Carry the data in the form to trigger the submit event,event.detail = {value : {'name': 'value'} , formId: ''}
defs/html/uni_vue_tag._.event.tap.description: Leave immediately after the finger touches
defs/html/uni_vue_tag._.event.timeupdate.description: Triggered when the playback progress changes,event.detail = {currentTime, duration} 。Trigger frequency 250ms once
defs/html/uni_vue_tag._.event.touchcancel.description: Interrupted finger touch action, such as call reminder, pop-up window
defs/html/uni_vue_tag._.event.transition.description: The transition event is triggered when the swiper-item position is changed,event.detail = {dx: dx, dy: dy}
defs/html/uni_vue_tag._.event.updated.description: Triggered when the map rendering update is complete
defs/html/uni_vue_tag._.event.waiting.description: Triggered when the video is buffered

defs/html/vue_html._.attribute.appear.description: Whether to use transitions during initial rendering. The default is false.
defs/html/vue_html._.attribute.css.description: Whether to use CSS transition classes. The default is true. If set to false, the registered JavaScript hook will only be triggered through component events.
defs/html/vue_html._.attribute.duration.description: Specify the duration of the transition. By default, Vue will wait for the first transitionend or animationend event of the root element of the transition.
defs/html/vue_html._.attribute.exclude.description: String or regular expression. Any components with matching names will not be cached.
defs/html/vue_html._.attribute.include.description: String or regular expression. Only components with matching names will be cached.
defs/html/vue_html._.attribute.max.description: The maximum number of component instances that can be cached.
defs/html/vue_html._.attribute.mode.description: Control the transition time sequence of departure/entry. The valid modes are "out-in" and "in-out"; both are effective by default.
defs/html/vue_html._.attribute.move-class.description: Override CSS classes applied during the mobile transition.
defs/html/vue_html._.attribute.name.description: Used to automatically generate CSS transition class names. For example: name:'fade' will automatically expand to .fade-enter, .fade-enter-active, etc. The default class name is "v"
defs/html/vue_html._.attribute.type.description: Specify the transition event type and listen for when the transition ends. The valid values are "transition" and "animation". By default, Vue.js will automatically detect the transition event type with a long duration.
defs/html/vue_html._.attribute.v-bind.description:
Dynamically bind one or more properties, or a component prop to an expression.
When binding class or style attributes, other types of values, such as arrays or objects, are supported. You can check the details through the tutorial link below.
When binding props, props must be declared in child components. You can specify different binding types with modifiers.
When there are no parameters, it can be bound to an object containing key-value pairs. Note that the class and style bindings do not support arrays and objects at this time.
reference:
https://cn.vuejs.org/v2/api/#v-bind
defs/html/vue_html._.attribute.v-bind.example:
<!-- Bind a property -->
<img v-bind:src="imageSrc">

<!-- abbreviation -->
<img :src="imageSrc">

<!-- Inline string concatenation -->
<img :src="'/path/to/images/' + fileName">

<!-- class Bind -->
<div :class="{ red: isRed }"></div>
<div :class="[classA, classB]"></div>
<div :class="[classA, { classB: isB, classC: isC }]">

<!-- style Bind -->
<div :style="{ fontSize: size + 'px' }"></div>
<div :style="[styleObjectA, styleObjectB]"></div>

<!-- Bind an object with attributes -->
<div v-bind="{ id: someProp, 'other-attr': otherProp }"></div>

<!-- Binding DOM properties through prop modifier-->
<div v-bind:text-content.prop="text"></div>

<!-- prop Bind Declared in my-component.-->
<my-component :prop="someThing"></my-component>

<!-- Pass the props of the parent component to the child component through $props -->
<child-component v-bind="$props"></child-component>

<!-- XLink -->
<svg><a :xlink:special="foo"></a></svg>
defs/html/vue_html._.attribute.v-cloak.description:
This instruction remains on the element until the associated instance finishes compiling. When used with CSS rules such as [v-cloak] {display: none }, this command can hide uncompiled Mustache tags until the instance is ready.
reference:
https://cn.vuejs.org/v2/api/#v-cloak
defs/html/vue_html._.attribute.v-else-if.description:
The previous sibling element must have v-if or v-else-if.
Reference:
https://cn.vuejs.org/v2/api/#v-else-if
defs/html/vue_html._.attribute.v-else.description:
No expression is required, the previous sibling element must have v-if or v-else-if.
reference:
https://cn.vuejs.org/v2/api/#v-else
defs/html/vue_html._.attribute.v-for.description:
Render the element or template block multiple times based on the source data.
reference:
List rendering
reference:
https://cn.vuejs.org/v2/api/#v-for
defs/html/vue_html._.attribute.v-html.description:
Update the innerHTML of the element. Note: The content is inserted as normal HTML-it will not be compiled as a Vue template. If you try to use the v-html composite template, you can reconsider whether to use components instead.
reference:
https://cn.vuejs.org/v2/api/#v-html
defs/html/vue_html._.attribute.v-html.remarks: Dynamic rendering of arbitrary HTML on a website is very dangerous because it can easily lead to XSS attacks. Only use v-html on trusted content, never on content submitted by users.
defs/html/vue_html._.attribute.v-if.description: The element is rendered based on the true or false condition of the value of the expression. When switching, the element and its data binding/component are destroyed and rebuilt. If the element is a
defs/html/vue_html._.attribute.v-model.description:
Create two-way bindings on form controls or components. Please see the tutorial link below for details.
reference:
https://cn.vuejs.org/v2/api/#v-model
reference:
Form control binding
reference:
组件 - 在输入组件上使用自定义事件
defs/html/vue_html._.attribute.v-on.description:
Bind event listeners. The event type is specified by the parameter. The expression can be the name of a method or an inline statement, or it can be omitted if there is no modifier.
When used on common elements, only native DOM events can be monitored. When used on custom element components, you can also listen to custom events triggered by subcomponents.
When listening to native DOM events, the method takes the event as the only parameter. If you use an inline statement, the statement can access a $event attribute: v-on:click="handle('ok', $event)".
Starting from 2.4.0, v-on also supports binding an event/listener key-value pair object without parameters. Note that when using object syntax, no decorators are supported.
reference:
https://cn.vuejs.org/v2/api/#v-on
defs/html/vue_html._.attribute.v-on.example:
<!-- Method handler -->
<button v-on:click="doThis"></button>

<!-- Inline statement -->
<button v-on:click="doThat('hello', $event)"></button>

<!-- abbreviation -->
<button @click="doThis"></button>

<!-- Stop bubbling -->
<button @click.stop="doThis"></button>

<!-- Prevent default behavior -->
<button @click.prevent="doThis"></button>

<!-- Prevent default behavior, no expression -->
<form @submit.prevent></form>

<!--  Concatenation modifier -->
<button @click.stop.prevent="doThis"></button>

<!-- Key modifier, key alias -->
<input @keyup.enter="onEnter">

<!-- Key modifier, key code -->
<input @keyup.13="onEnter">

<!-- Click callback will only be triggered once -->
<button v-on:click.once="doThis"></button>

<!-- Object syntax (2.4.0+) -->
<button v-on="{ mousedown: doThis, mouseup: doThat }"></button>
defs/html/vue_html._.attribute.v-once.description:
Only render elements and components once. Subsequent re-rendering, the element/component and all its child nodes will be treated as static content and skipped. This can be used to optimize update performance.
reference:
https://cn.vuejs.org/v2/api/#v-once
defs/html/vue_html._.attribute.v-once.example:
<!-- Single element -->
<span v-once>This will never change: {{msg}}</span>
<!-- Has child elements  -->
<div v-once>
  <h1>comment</h1>
  <p>{{msg}}</p>
</div>
<!-- Component -->
<my-component v-once :comment="msg"></my-component>
<!-- `v-for` instruction-->
<ul>
  <li v-for="i in list" v-once>{{i}}</li>
</ul>
defs/html/vue_html._.attribute.v-pre.description:
Skip the compilation process of this element and its child elements. Can be used to display original Mustache tags. Skipping a large number of nodes without instructions will speed up compilation.
reference:
https://cn.vuejs.org/v2/api/#v-pre
defs/html/vue_html._.attribute.v-pre.example: {{ this will not be compiled }}
defs/html/vue_html._.attribute.v-show.description:
According to the true and false value of the expression, switch the display CSS property of the element. This instruction triggers the transition effect when the conditions change.
reference:
https://cn.vuejs.org/v2/api/#v-show
defs/html/vue_html._.attribute.v-text.description:
Update the textContent of the element. If you want to update part of the textContent, you need to use {{ Mustache }} interpolation.
Starting from 2.4.0, v-on also supports binding an event/listener key-value pair object without parameters. Note that when using object syntax, no decorators are supported.
reference:
https://cn.vuejs.org/v2/api/#v-text
defs/html/vue_html._.element.component.description: Render a "meta component" as a dynamic component. Depending on the value of "is", it determines which component is rendered.
defs/html/vue_html._.element.keep-alive.description: <keep-alive> When wrapping dynamic components, inactive component instances are cached instead of destroying them. Similar to <transition>, <keep-alive> is an abstract component: it does not render a DOM element by itself, nor does it appear in the parent component chain.
defs/html/vue_html._.element.slot.description: <slot> The element serves as a content distribution slot in the component template. The <slot> element itself will be replaced.
defs/html/vue_html._.element.transition-group.description: <transition-group> The element acts as a transition effect of multiple elements/components. <transition-group> renders a real DOM element. The default rendering <span>, you can configure which element should be rendered through the tag attribute.
defs/html/vue_html._.element.transition.description: <transition> The element acts as a transition effect of a single element/component. <transition> will only apply the transition effect to the content it wraps, and will not render additional DOM elements, nor will it appear in the detected component level.

defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.auto-play.description: The optional values are true/false, and the default is false. This value determines whether to automatically play the carousel. Reset the UI related to loadmore. If the value is different, it will be reset.
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.autofocus.description: Boolean data, indicating whether the control automatically gets the input focus when the page loads.
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.case.description:
The type of the current template is declared. It will be rendered only when the type in the data matches the current type. The semantics are consistent with the case in the programming language.

At most, only one item can be matched among all the templates, which are matched from top to bottom in the order of the templates. Once the match is successful, it will not continue to match the next one.
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.column-count.description: Describe the number of columns in the waterfall
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.column-gap.description: The gap between columns. If normal is specified, it corresponds to 32.
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.column-width.description: Describe the column width of each column of the waterfall
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.default.description: Indicates that the current template is the default template type and does not need to specify a value. If the data item does not match any case type, the default template is rendered. If there are multiple defaults, only the first default template will be used.
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.disabled.description: Boolean data, indicating whether input is supported. Usually the click event is invalid on disabled controls.
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.for.description:
Add the for attribute to recycle-list to describe how to recycle the data in the list.
The syntax is similar to Vue's v-for instruction, but it loops through its own internal child nodes, not the current node.

The for attribute supports the following two writing methods:

alias in expression
(alias, index) in expression
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.href.description: The URL of the page to be redirected. The page to be redirected needs to be a Weex page. If the page to be redirected is a normal HTML, this will be an undefined behavior.
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.index.description: Set which page to display the slider
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.infinite.description: Loop playback, the optional value is true/false, the default is true.
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.interval.description: The value is milliseconds. This value sets the slider switching time interval. It takes effect when the auto-play value is true.
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.keep-index.description: Set whether to keep the index of the page before the change after the data in the slider changes
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.keep-scroll-position.descrip: Whether to keep the last scrolled position after inserting data in List
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.key.description: Optional attribute, used to specify the key value that can be used as a unique identifier in the list data, and can optimize the rendering performance.
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.left-gap.description: The gap between the left cell and the list. If not specified, it corresponds to 0
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.lines.description: Control the maximum number of lines of input
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.loadmoreoffset.description: The default value is 0，The vertical offset distance (the distance between the bottom of the device screen and the bottom of the list) required to trigger the loadmore event. The loadmore event will be triggered when the scroll bar of the list is sufficiently close to the bottom of the list.
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.max-length.description: Control the maximum length of input
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.max.description: Control the maximum time for selecting a date when the type attribute is date, the format is yyyy-MM-dd
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.maxlength.description: A numeric value that represents the maximum length of the input.
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.min.description: Control the minimum time for selecting a date when the type attribute is date, the format is yyyy-MM-dd
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.offset-accuracy.description: Controls how often the onscroll event is triggered. The default value is 10, which means that the list has scrolled at least 10px between two onscroll events. Note that setting this value to a smaller value will improve the accuracy of scroll event sampling, but it will also reduce page performance.
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.offset-x-accuracy.descriptio: Controls how often the onscroll event is triggered. The default value is 10, which means that the Slider Page has scrolled at least 10px between onscroll events. Note that setting this value to a smaller value will improve the accuracy of scroll event sampling, but it will also reduce page performance.
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.placeholder.description:
When used as an image attribute, it means:
The URL of the placeholder image will be deleted when the image represented by src is downloaded and displayed. Example
When used as an attribute of input, it means:
Prompt the user what to enter. The prompt text cannot have carriage returns or line feeds.
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.play-status.description: The optional values are play | pause, which is used to control the playback state of the video, play or pause, and the default value is pause.
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.return-key-type.description: The type of keyboard return key supports defalut;go;next;search;send,done.
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.right-gap.description: The gap between the right cell and the list. If not specified, it corresponds to 0
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.rows.description: Receive number type data, specify the height of the component, the default value is 2
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.scroll-direction.description: It can be horizontal or vertical, and the default value is vertical. Define the direction of scrolling.
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.scrollable.description: Set whether the slider page can be switched by sliding gestures
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.show-scrollbar.description: Optional values are true/false, and the default value is true. Control whether scroll bars appear.
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.singleline.description: Control whether only single line is allowed
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.src.description: The URL of the image to be displayed. This attribute is mandatory for the <image> component.
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.switch.description:
Adding the switch attribute to the recycle-list can be used to specify the field name used to distinguish the molecular template type in the data. The semantics are consistent with the switch in the programming language, and it is used together with the case and default attributes in the cell-slot.

If the switch attribute is omitted, only the first cell-slot will be regarded as a template, and redundant templates will be ignored.
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.type.description: Input type, does not support dynamic modification, default is text
defs/html/weex_html._.attribute.value.description: The default content of the component.
defs/html/weex_html._.element.cell-slot.description: cell-slot It represents the template of each item in the list. It is only used to describe the structure of the template and does not correspond to the actual node. The number of cell-slot only represents the number of template types, and the number of real list items is determined by the data.
defs/html/weex_html._.element.cell.description:
Used to define the sub-list items in the list, similar to the ul to li in HTML. Weex will perform efficient memory recycling on the cell to achieve better performance. This component must be a subcomponent of the list recycler waterfall component, which is to optimize the performance during scrolling.
reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/cell.html
defs/html/weex_html._.element.div.description:
The div component is the most basic container for packaging other components. Support all common styles, features, flexbox layouts. It is similar to the HTML div container, but you cannot add text (string) directly in it. If you want to display text, you should use the text component. In the historical version, the alias of div is container, which is currently deprecated。
reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/div.html
defs/html/weex_html._.element.div.remarks: <div> The nesting level cannot be too deep, otherwise it will easily cause performance problems. It is recommended to control it within 10 levels.
defs/html/weex_html._.element.image.description:
image is used to display a single picture in the interface.
reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/image.html
defs/html/weex_html._.element.image.remarks: Note: The width and height in the style must be specified, otherwise it will not work.
defs/html/weex_html._.element.indicator.description: The indicator component is usually used to display the indicator effect of the carousel and must be used as a subcomponent of the slider component.
defs/html/weex_html._.element.input.description:
Weex's built-in input component is used to create an input component that receives characters input by the user. The working mode of the input component varies depending on the value of the type attribute, such as text, password, url, email, tel, etc.
reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/input.html
defs/html/weex_html._.element.input.remarks: This component does not support the click event. Please listen to input or change instead of click event.
defs/html/weex_html._.element.list.description:
The list component is the core component that provides the vertical list function, with smooth scrolling and efficient memory management, which is very suitable for displaying long lists. The simplest way to use it is to fill the list tag with a set of cell tags generated by a simple array repeat.
reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/list.html
defs/html/weex_html._.element.loading.description:
loading Provides a pull-up loading function for the container, usage and attributes are similar to refresh.
reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/loading.html
defs/html/weex_html._.element.recycle-list.description:
recycle-list is a new list container with the ability to recycle and reuse, which can greatly optimize memory usage and rendering performance. Only cell-slot can be used as its direct child node, and other nodes are invalid.
reference:
https://uniapp.dcloud.io/component/recycle-list
defs/html/weex_html._.element.recycle-list.example:
The usage in the upper grammar is as follows: 

<recycle-list for="(item, i) in longList" switch="type">
  <cell-slot case="A">
    <text>- A {{i}} -</text>
  </cell-slot>
  <cell-slot case="B">
    <text>- B {{i}} -</text>
  </cell-slot>
</recycle-list>
如果有如下数据：

const longList = [
  { type: 'A' },
  { type: 'B' },
  { type: 'B' },
  { type: 'A' },
  { type: 'B' }
]
Will generate the following equivalent nodes: 

<text>- A 0 -</text>
<text>- B 1 -</text>
<text>- B 2 -</text>
<text>- A 3 -</text>
<text>- B 4 -</text>
defs/html/weex_html._.element.refresh.description:
refresh Provide a drop-down refresh function for the container, usage and attributes are similar to loading.
reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/refresh.html
defs/html/weex_html._.element.scroller.description:
scroller It is a vertical scroller that can accommodate multiple sub-components arranged in a row. If the total height of the sub-component is higher than itself, then all the sub-components can be scrolled.
reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/scroller.html
defs/html/weex_html._.element.slider.description:
The slider component is used to display multiple pictures on a page. On the front end, this effect is called a carousel.
reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/slider.html
defs/html/weex_html._.element.text.description:
text is a built-in component of Weex, which is used to render text in a specified style. text can only contain text values, you can use {{}} tags to insert variable values as text content.
reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/text.html
defs/html/weex_html._.element.text.remarks: If you need to keep the head and tail blanks, you can only write the head and tail blanks through data binding temporarily.
defs/html/weex_html._.element.textarea.description:
textarea is a built-in component of Weex, used for user interaction and accepting user input data. It can be considered as allowing multiple lines of input
reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/textarea.html
defs/html/weex_html._.element.textarea.remarks: textarea supports all events supported by input.
defs/html/weex_html._.element.video.description:
The video component allows us to embed video content in Weex pages.
reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/video.html
defs/html/weex_html._.element.waterfall.description:
Provide components for waterfall flow layout
reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/waterfall.html
defs/html/weex_html._.element.web.description:
web is used to display the page content specified by the src attribute in the weex page. You can also use the webview module to control the behavior of the WebView, such as back, forward, and reload. For more information, see webview module.
reference:
http://weex.apache.org/cn/references/components/web.html
defs/html/weex_html._.event.appear.description: If a component located in a scrollable area is bound to the appear event, the event will be triggered when the state of the component becomes visible on the screen.
defs/html/weex_html._.event.change.description: Triggered when user input is complete. Usually after the blur event.
defs/html/weex_html._.event.click.description: Triggered when a click gesture occurs on the component.
defs/html/weex_html._.event.disappear.description: If a component in a scrollable area is bound to the disappear event, the event will be triggered when the component is slid out of the screen and becomes invisible.
defs/html/weex_html._.event.error.description: The error event is called when the Web page fails to load.
defs/html/weex_html._.event.fail.description: Triggered when the playback status is Failed
defs/html/weex_html._.event.finish.description: Triggered when the playback status is Finished
defs/html/weex_html._.event.focus.description: The component gets the input focus.
defs/html/weex_html._.event.input.description: The value of the input character changes.
defs/html/weex_html._.event.load.description: When the load is complete src When the specified picture, the load event will be triggered.
defs/html/weex_html._.event.loading.description: Triggered when it is pulled up.
defs/html/weex_html._.event.loadmore.description: If the list scrolls to the bottom, this event will be triggered immediately, and you can load the list items of the next page in the event handler.
defs/html/weex_html._.event.longpress.description: If a component is bound to a longpress event, then when the user long presses the component, the event will be triggered.
defs/html/weex_html._.event.pagefinish.description: The pagefinish event is called when the web page has finished loading.
defs/html/weex_html._.event.pagestart.description: The pagestart event is called when the web page starts to load.
defs/html/weex_html._.event.pause.description: Triggered when the playback status is Paused
defs/html/weex_html._.event.pullingdown.description:
Triggered when it is pulled down, you can get dy, pullingDistance, viewHeight, type from the event parameter object 
dy: The difference between the sliding distance of the two callbacks before and after
pullingDistance: pulling distance
viewHeight: refresh component height
type: "pullingdown" constant string
defs/html/weex_html._.event.receivedtitle.description: The receivedtitle event will be called when the title of the Web page changes (Android platform only).
defs/html/weex_html._.event.refresh.description: Triggered when it is pulled down.
defs/html/weex_html._.event.return.description: Press the return key on the keyboard.
defs/html/weex_html._.event.scroll.description: This event will be triggered when the list is scrolled. The default sampling rate of the event is 10px, which means it will be triggered every time the list is scrolled 10px. The sampling rate can be set through the attribute offset-accuracy。
defs/html/weex_html._.event.scrollend.description: Fires when the list ends scrolling.
defs/html/weex_html._.event.scrollstart.description: Fires when the list starts to scroll.
defs/html/weex_html._.event.start.description: Triggered when the state of playback is Playing
defs/html/weex_html._.event.viewappear.description: viewappear The event will be triggered before any page animations to be displayed or configured on the page are executed.

HTML5 + interface, unifies browser custom extension, provides enhanced function and performance extension specification, so that developers can develop cross platform apps, and approach native function and performance.

The accelerator module manages the acceleration sensor of the device, which is used to obtain the acceleration information of the device, including the acceleration information of X (horizontal direction of the screen), y (horizontal direction of the vertical screen) and Z (plane direction of the vertical screen). adopt plus.accelerometer Get the device acceleration sensor management object.

The ad module realizes the uni ad advertising alliance function, aggregates the popular domestic advertising platforms, such as Tencent, pangolin, 360 advertising, and supports information flow, banner and other advertising.
Native.js  For Android encapsulates a way to call native java interface directly through JS syntax plus.android It can call almost all system APIs.

The audio module is used to provide audio recording and playback functions. It can call the microphone device of the system for recording operation, and also call the speaker device of the system to play audio files. adopt plus.audio Gets the audio management object.

Barcode module manages barcode (one-dimensional code and two-dimensional code) scanning and recognition, supports common one-dimensional code (such as EAN13 code) and two-dimensional code (such as QR code). By calling the camera of the device to scan and identify the barcode, decode the barcode and return the code data content and code type.
Bluetooth module is used to manage Bluetooth devices, search nearby Bluetooth devices and realize simple data transmission.
The camera module manages the camera of the device, which can be used to take pictures and take pictures plus.camera Get the camera management object.

The contacts module manages the address book of the system, which is used to add, delete, modify and check the address book of the system. adopt plus.contacts Get the system address book management object.

The device module manages the device information, which is used to obtain the relevant information of mobile devices, such as IMEI, IMSI, model, manufacturer, etc. adopt plus.device Get the device information management object.
The display module manages the display area information that can be used by the application

The downloader module manages the network file download task, which is used to download various files from the server, and supports cross domain access operation. adopt plus.downloader Get the download management object. Downloader download uses HTTP get / post to request the download file, which conforms to the standard HTTP / HTTPS transport protocol.

Gallery module manages the album of the system, supports the functions of selecting pictures or video files from the album, saving pictures or video files to the album, etc. adopt plus.gallery Gets the album management object.

The geolocation module manages the location information of the device, which is used to obtain the geographic location information, such as longitude, latitude and so on. adopt plus.geolocation Get the device location management object. Although W3C has provided standard API to obtain location information, there are differences or not implemented in some platforms. In order to maintain the unity of various platforms, this specification interface is defined to obtain location information.
The ibeacon module is used to search ibeacon devices for attachments.
IO module manages the local file system, which is used to browse the directory of the file system, read and write files. adopt plus.io Gets the file system management object.
Native.js  For IOS encapsulates an interface channel that directly calls native Objective-C through JS syntax plus.ios It can call almost all system APIs.

The maps module manages the map control, which is used to display the map control in the web page, and provides various interfaces to operate the map control, such as adding punctuation, route and so on. adopt plus.maps Map management objects can be obtained.

The messaging module manages the device communication function, which can be used for SMS, MMS, e-mail sending, etc. adopt plus.messaging Can get the device communication management object. In addition, you can also send short messages, make phone calls and send e-mails directly and quickly through the HTML.
Native obj management system native object.
Native UI management system native interface can be used to pop up the system native prompt dialog box window, time and date selection dialog box, waiting dialog box, etc.
Navigator is used to manage the running environment information of browser

The XMLHttpRequest module manages network requests, which is consistent with the use of XMLHttpRequest in standard HTML. The difference is that the former can carry out cross domain access. adopt plus.net Get the network request management object.
The networkinfo module is used to obtain network information
OAuth module manages the user login authentication function of the client, and allows the application to access the resources of the third-party platform.
The orientation module manages the direction information of the device, including alpha, beta and gamma plus.orientation The device direction management object can be obtained.
OS module manages operating system information

The payment module manages the payment function, which is used to provide web page security payment ability and support payment operation through web interface. adopt plus.payment Access to payment management objects.

The proximity module manages the distance sensor of the device, which can obtain the proximity information of the current device plus.proximity The device distance sensing management object can be obtained.
Push module management push message function, can achieve online, offline message push, through the plus.push The push message management object can be obtained.

The runtime module manages the running environment, which can be used to obtain the current running environment information and communicate with other programs. adopt plus.runtime Gets the runtime environment management object.
Screen module manages device screen information
The share module manages the social sharing function of the client and provides the sharing ability to call the terminal social software. adopt plus.share Access to social sharing management objects.

Speech module manages speech input function, provides speech recognition function, and supports users to input speech content through microphone device. adopt plus.speech The voice input management object can be obtained.
SQLite module is used to operate local database files, which can create database files and execute SQL statements.

Statistics module is used to manage statistics function, which is used to provide the ability of statistics within the application, and support the statistics and analysis of user attributes and user behavior data. adopt plus.statistic The statistics management object can be obtained.

The storage module manages the application local data storage area, which is used to save and read the application data. The difference between application local data and local storage and session storage is that the data valid domain is different. The former can operate across domains within the application, and the data storage period is persistent, and there is no capacity limit. adopt plus.storage The local data management object of the application can be obtained.
The stream module operates the stream application.

Uploader module manages the network upload task, which is used to upload various files from local to server, and supports cross domain access operation. adopt plus.uploader The upload management object can be obtained. Uploader uploads and submits data in HTTP post mode. The data format conforms to multipart / form data specification, namely rfc1867 (form based file upload in HTML) protocol.
The video module can manage multimedia video related capabilities, such as creating video playback controls, live streaming controls, etc.

The WebView module manages the application window interface and realizes the logical control and management operation of multiple windows. adopt plus.webview The application interface management object can be obtained.
Zip module manages the compression and decompression of files plus.zip Gets the compressed management object.

converts a date/time string into a date object.

defs/js/uniCloud_server_js.AggregateCommand_.method.isoWeekYear.des: Returns the ISO 8601 standard days (day of the year) corresponding to the date field.
